EXP4 :

git clone <forked-repo-url>                # Clone the forked repository from GitHub to local system
git branch feature-1                      # Create a new feature branch named feature-1
git checkout feature-1                    # Switch to the feature-1 branch for development
git add .                                # Stage all modified and new files for commit
git commit -m "Changes done in feature-1" # Save changes in feature-1 branch with a message
git push origin feature-1                 # Push the feature branch to GitHub repository
git checkout master                      # Switch back to master branch (or main if used)
git pull origin master                   # Update local master branch with latest remote changes
git branch -d feature-1                  # Delete local feature branch after merge (optional)
git push origin --delete feature-1       # Delete feature branch from GitHub repository (optional)



EXP 5:


git checkout main                     # Switch to the main branch to ensure tagging is done on latest stable code
git pull                              # Update local repository with latest changes from remote
git tag v1.0                          # Create a lightweight tag v1.0 pointing to current commit
git tag                               # List all tags in the local repository
git tag -a v1.2 -m "v1.2 Created"     # Create an annotated tag v1.2 with a descriptive message
git tag                               # Verify that the annotated tag appears in the list
git show v1.0                         # Display detailed information about tag v1.0 including commit details
git tag -l "v1.*"                     # List all tags that match pattern v1.*
git push origin v1.2                  # Push specific tag v1.2 to remote GitHub repository
git push origin --tags                # Push all local tags to remote repository at once
